</div><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the first diagram, the word =E2=80=9C=
controls=E2=80=9D appears four times, and if you trace it=C2=A0through,=C2=
=A0you will see that the board of directors of OpenAI ultimately=C2=A0contr=
ols each entity in the organization. All of=C2=A0OpenAI answers to its ulti=
mate decision-making body, an=C2=A0independent nonprofit board of directors=
 who do not own any equity in the OpenAI entities and who, broadly speaking=
, appoint themselves. They answer to their own consciences, not to any inve=
stors. =E2=80=9CThe Nonprofit=E2=80=99s principal beneficiary is humanity, =
not OpenAI investors,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/33431564.256422/aHR0cHM6Ly9vcGVuYWkuY29tL291ci1zdHJ1Y3R1cmU/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCbd47c5bb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> explains OpenAI</a>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the second diagram, I have written the word=
 =E2=80=9CMONEY=E2=80=9D in large green letters.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The question is: Is control of OpenAI=C2=A0ind=
icated by the word =E2=80=9Ccontrols,=E2=80=9D or by the word =E2=80=9CMONE=
Y=E2=80=9D?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Friday, OpenAI=E2=80=99s nonprofit board, i=
ts ultimate decision maker, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/33431564.256422/aHR0cHM6Ly9vcGVuYWkuY29tL2Jsb2cvb3BlbmFpLWFubm91b=
mNlcy1sZWFkZXJzaGlwLXRyYW5zaXRpb24/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4f8dfba8" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;"> fired Sam Altman</a>, its co-founder and chief executive officer, sayin=
g that =E2=80=9Che was not consistently candid in his communications with t=
he board, hindering its ability to exercise its responsibilities.=E2=80=9D =
Apparently the board felt that Altman was moving too aggressively to commer=
cialize OpenAI=E2=80=99s products like ChatGPT, and worried that this speed=
 of commercialization raised the risk of creating a rogue artificial intell=
igence that would, you know, murder or enslave humanity.<a class=3D"footnot=
e-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; =
display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So it just fired him. =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33431564.256422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY=
mxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMjAvbWljcm9zb2Z0LXNheXMtYWx0=
bWFuLWJyb2NrbWFuLXdpbGwtbGVhZC1uZXctaW4taG91c2UtYWktdGVhbT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTI=
wMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG=
