=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  conditions for coming back</a>, as far as I can tell, were t=
hat the board had to resign and the governance had to change; I take that t=
o mean roughly that OpenAI had to become a normal tech company with him as =
a typically powerful founder-CEO. They <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/33431564.256422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlaW5mb3JtYXRpb24uY2=
9tL2FydGljbGVzL29wZW5haS1vcHRpbWlzdGljLWl0LWNhbi1icmluZy1iYWNrLXNhbS1hbHRtY=
W4tZ3JlZy1icm9ja21hbg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB80644cdc" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> almost go=
t there</a>, but then did not. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/33431564.256422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydG=
ljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMjAvb3BlbmFpLXMtYm9hcmQtaGlyZXMtZm9ybWVyLXR3aXRjaC1leGVjd=
XRpdmUtc2hlYXItYXMtY2VvP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMjAyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09=
ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTEyMCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ24=
9bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcada9036" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  This morning</=
a>, OpenAI announced that Emmett Shear, the former CEO of Twitch, would be =
its new interim CEO, while Microsoft announced that it had hired Altman to =
lead its in-house artificial intelligence efforts.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/33431564.256422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXhpb3MuY29tLzIwMjMvMTEvMjAvb3Bl=
bmFpLXN0YWZmLWxldHRlci1ib2FyZC1yZXNpZ24tc2FtLWFsdG1hbg/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB7284fda6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">Also this morning</a>, =E2=80=9Cmore than 500 of Ope=
nAI's 700-plus employees signed an open letter urging OpenAI's board to res=
ign=E2=80=9D and threatening to quit to join Altman=E2=80=99s Microsoft tea=
m. Incredibly, one of the signers of that letter is Ilya Sutskever, OpenAI=
=E2=80=99s chief scientist, who is on the board and apparently led the effo=
