<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Everyone understands the basic deal for invest=
ment banking analysts. The good news is that they=C2=A0get prestige, a nice=
 paycheck, good exit options and=C2=A0intense training in financial modelin=
g and dealmaking. The bad news is that they work too much, are always at th=
e office, can=E2=80=99t make social plans and don=E2=80=99t get much sleep.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are a smart ambitious young person you =
might think to yourself =E2=80=9CI would like the upsides of that deal, but=
 without the downsides.=E2=80=9D In recent years, we have seen analysts at =
a number of banks try to renegotiate the deal. At Goldman Sachs Group Inc. =
a few years ago, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
3431564.256422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIw=
MjEtMDMtMTgvZ29sZG1hbi1hbmFseXN0cy13b3JrLXRvby1oYXJkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMjAyM19=
NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZX=
JtPTIzMTEyMCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc29c7=
853" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  they wrote a whole pitchbook</a> being like =E2=80=9Cwe shou=
ld be able to go home sometimes.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An approach that honestly never occurred to me=
 is: If you get a=C2=A0<em>doctor=E2=80=99s note=C2=A0</em>saying that you =
need eight hours of sleep every night, does the bank have to let you go hom=
e at midnight? Like:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It does seem like a bad look for the b=
ank not to=C2=A0respect doctor=E2=80=99s=C2=A0notes?</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">What doctor is going to say you=C2=A0<em>don=E2=80=99t=
=C2=A0</em>need eight hours of sleep?</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Promising. At the Financial Times, <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33431564.256422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvNGY4YmY4ZWQtNDhhYS00ZTU1LTgzOTYtMzRmMmZmODg3YzZj/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7510abb7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Sujeet Indap reports</a> that a (f=
ormer) Centerview Partners analyst named Kate Shiber tried it, so far=C2=A0=
without much success:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">She told the firm=E2=80=99s human resources de=
partment about her medical condition and a therapeutic need to get eight to=
 nine hours of sleep a night, later confirmed by a nurse=E2=80=99s note. Ce=
nterview immediately expressed compassion for her and implemented what it r=
eferred to as =E2=80=9Cguardrails=E2=80=9D, a daily nine-hour window starti=
ng at midnight where she was excused from her work duties.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Less than three weeks later in September 2020,=
 Shiber was summoned to a video meeting where two Centerview administrators=
 fired her, tersely informing her the firm could no longer accommodate her =
sleep requirement. She has subsequently sued Centerview, accusing the firm =
of violating federal and state anti-discrimination laws that she believes a=
pply to her based on her mental illness diagnoses. She is requesting $5mn i=
n damages.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Centerview said it was within its rights to te=
rminate Shiber, claiming that she simply could not meet a basic requirement=
 of a demanding job while the firm also said it worried about the health co=
nsequences if she stayed.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Harsh, and yet you can see where they are comi=
ng from. Working investment banking hours isn=E2=80=99t good for anyone, an=
d if you create a precedent like =E2=80=9Cyou don=E2=80=99t have to work al=
l night if you need sleep=E2=80=9D then who will work all night?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway after she was fired Shiber seems to hav=
e taken a third popular approach to getting the benefits of the investment =
banking job without the downsides: =E2=80=9CShe now is a financial analyst =
at Google in California where her day wraps up between 5pm and 8pm.=E2=80=
=9D Seems like a good job!</p>
